// Base Debug configuration for the Mural app target.
//
// macOS ties privacy (TCC) grants such as Screen Recording to an app's code
// signing identity. An ad-hoc signature has no stable identity, so the grant is
// keyed on the binary hash, which changes on every rebuild and forces the
// permission prompt to reappear. Signing Debug with a real identity keeps the
// grant across rebuilds.
//
// To enable that locally, create a gitignored Config/Local.xcconfig with your
// signing identity (see CONTRIBUTING.md). When the file is absent this include
// is skipped and the Debug build stays ad-hoc, so the repo and CI are
// unaffected.
#include? "Local.xcconfig"
